about.summary: A toolbox for R arrays. Flexibly split, bind, reshape, modify,  subset and name arrays.

name: r-listarrays
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.3.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-listarrays
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/listarrays_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/listarrays/listarrays_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9a465f452e743019b445a3906098be17bc8420e01278638af489de84b9c7d759

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('listarrays')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('listarrays')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/t-kalinowski/listarrays, https://t-kalinowski.github.io/listarrays/
  license: GPL-3
  summary: A toolbox for R arrays. Flexibly split, bind, reshape, modify,  subset and name arrays.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
